00:00:22.530 --> 00:00:25.470
MICHAEL SHORT: So, before we
begin today's bit on dose,

00:00:25.470 --> 00:00:27.180
dosimetry, and
background radiation,

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:28.770
I promised you guys
a story about how

00:00:28.770 --> 00:00:32.409
to use 22.01 to get out of
Apartheid, South Africa.

00:00:32.409 --> 00:00:35.910
So, I got told this story when
my cousin was about to get

00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:39.480
married because he needed a
diamond and he was going to go

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:42.430
buy one and his dad said, don't.

00:00:42.430 --> 00:00:46.870
So back in the 70s, when
my uncle and his family

00:00:46.870 --> 00:00:48.460
were living in
South Africa, anyone

00:00:48.460 --> 00:00:51.190
who wasn't Dutch white,
so that would be blacks,

00:00:51.190 --> 00:00:54.010
Jews, including
us, anyone else was

00:00:54.010 --> 00:00:57.252
considered second-class citizens
by the Apartheid Government.

00:00:57.252 --> 00:00:59.710
And you were allowed to leave,
because they didn't want you

00:00:59.710 --> 00:01:01.570
there, but you had to
surrender all of your funds

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:03.220
to the government
in order to leave,

00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:05.880
which gives me everything
you have and then

00:01:05.880 --> 00:01:07.630
you can leave the
country penniless is not

00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:09.280
a winning proposition.

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:13.270
So, my uncle and his brother
devised a pretty brilliant idea

00:01:13.270 --> 00:01:16.660
to get their funds out of
South Africa unnoticed.

00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:19.450
They were both dentists
or radiologists

00:01:19.450 --> 00:01:22.750
or some sort of medical doctor
that requires x-ray reading.

00:01:22.750 --> 00:01:26.015
So, one of them gave the
other one all of his money,

00:01:26.015 --> 00:01:28.390
then reported bank statements
to the Apartheid Government

00:01:28.390 --> 00:01:30.670
and said, I'm pretty
much penniless.

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:32.173
My practice went broke.

00:01:32.173 --> 00:01:33.340
I want to leave the country.

00:01:33.340 --> 00:01:35.050
And they said, OK,
get out of here.

00:01:35.050 --> 00:01:37.180
So he went to the
US, established

00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:40.180
a dental or radiological or
some other sort of practice,

00:01:40.180 --> 00:01:44.140
I forget which one, and
started requesting his brother,

00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:46.510
back in South Africa, to
send him x-rays to read

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:48.760
to help boost his business.

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:51.910
Because that was their actual
business, it was pretty legit.

00:01:51.910 --> 00:01:54.640
So then my uncle would
send him packets of x-rays

00:01:54.640 --> 00:01:57.220
to interpret and send back.

00:01:57.220 --> 00:01:59.950
Except that there would
be 10 x-rays on the front

00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:02.110
and 10 on the bottom,
and the middle 80

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:03.130
would be hollowed out.

00:02:03.130 --> 00:02:04.930
AUDIENCE: Oh!

00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:07.120
MICHAEL SHORT: Now that
would have ordinarily have

00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:10.690
tripped off alarms because
any change in density

00:02:10.690 --> 00:02:13.090
would trigger a change
in x-ray contrast.

00:02:13.090 --> 00:02:15.670
Because these packages were
being inspected by x-ray,

00:02:15.670 --> 00:02:17.968
and if it looked like
these x-rays were hollow

00:02:17.968 --> 00:02:19.510
and you were smuggling
something out,

00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:22.080
they'd be caught
and confiscated.

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:25.740
So what sort of materials
are valuable that you

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:28.620
find in South Africa,
that are pretty

00:02:28.620 --> 00:02:34.128
similar in x-ray contrast to
other light media like film?

00:02:34.128 --> 00:02:34.920
AUDIENCE: Diamonds.

00:02:34.920 --> 00:02:36.910
MICHAEL SHORT: Diamonds.

00:02:36.910 --> 00:02:39.940
So the remaining brother
went and converted

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:42.550
all of his life savings into
diamonds, which is something

00:02:42.550 --> 00:02:45.040
that you can do in South
Africa because this

00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:47.000
is where diamonds come from.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.660
He then slowly, over a
period of months or years,

00:02:49.660 --> 00:02:52.840
sent packets of hollow
x-rays full of diamonds

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:56.200
to his brother in the
states, knowing full well

00:02:56.200 --> 00:03:00.580
that the mass attenuation
coefficients of soft tissue

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:04.430
and carbon are pretty similar
and so are their densities.

00:03:04.430 --> 00:03:06.700
So their total
attenuation coefficients

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:08.950
are pretty similar, to.

00:03:08.950 --> 00:03:11.770
Let's pull those up
so we can check it.

00:03:11.770 --> 00:03:13.536
Carbon graphite.

00:03:13.536 --> 00:03:17.420
I'm going to add a new tab
and bring up soft tissue

00:03:17.420 --> 00:03:19.210
and we can compare them.

00:03:19.210 --> 00:03:22.850
Let's see, what's
the most similar--

00:03:22.850 --> 00:03:25.025
so long as you can see
it-- thing to film?

00:03:28.460 --> 00:03:31.140
What should we call film here?

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:32.468
X-ray film?

00:03:32.468 --> 00:03:34.760
AUDIENCE: I don't even know
what X-ray film [INAUDIBLE]

00:03:34.760 --> 00:03:35.870
MICHAEL SHORT:
Photographic emulsion.

00:03:35.870 --> 00:03:36.495
How about that?

00:03:36.495 --> 00:03:37.766
AUDIENCE: Kodak.

00:03:37.766 --> 00:03:39.586
MICHAEL SHORT: Is
there something Kodak?

00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:41.620
OK.

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:42.940
Kodak, standard nuclear.

00:03:42.940 --> 00:03:46.370
I don't think that sounds right.

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:49.610
Let's go with
polyethylene and plastic.

00:03:49.610 --> 00:03:52.220
Carbon, plastic.

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:53.765
Carbon, plastic.

00:03:53.765 --> 00:03:55.160
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:03:55.160 --> 00:03:57.590
MICHAEL SHORT: Carbon, plastic.

00:03:57.590 --> 00:03:59.840
Basically identical.

00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:02.480
So this is a way they were
able to smuggle wealth out

00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:04.980
of the country without
x-ray contrast tripping off

00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:05.480
the guards.

00:04:05.480 --> 00:04:06.980
And once all of
the slave savings

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:08.948
had been converted
into diamonds,

00:04:08.948 --> 00:04:11.240
he then went to the government
and said, I'm penniless.

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:12.387
My practice went broke.

00:04:12.387 --> 00:04:13.470
I want to get out of here.

00:04:13.470 --> 00:04:14.940
And they said, good riddance.

00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:15.860
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:04:15.860 --> 00:04:16.610
MICHAEL SHORT: Yeah.

00:04:16.610 --> 00:04:18.140
So they were able to
restart their life

00:04:18.140 --> 00:04:19.598
in the states with
all of the money

00:04:19.598 --> 00:04:21.015
that they had had
in South Africa.

00:04:21.015 --> 00:04:23.098
And when my cousin wanted
to get married and said,

00:04:23.098 --> 00:04:25.440
I'm thinking of buying a
diamond, my uncle just said oh,

00:04:25.440 --> 00:04:25.940
don't.

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:27.398
He's like, what,
don't get married?

00:04:27.398 --> 00:04:28.910
He said, no, don't
buy a diamond.

00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:30.743
Here, let me take you
to the diamond drawer.

00:04:30.743 --> 00:04:31.887
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:04:31.887 --> 00:04:32.720
MICHAEL SHORT: Yeah.

00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:34.670
Because there was some leftover.

00:04:34.670 --> 00:04:37.250
So he said, pick out
an extra diamond.

00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:40.370
And that's the story of my
cousin's engagement ring,

00:04:40.370 --> 00:04:42.620
as well as why part of my
family's here in the States.

00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:45.260
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] That's
like a very cool diamond story.

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:49.200
MICHAEL SHORT: Yeah, very,
very nuclear diamond story.

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:51.510
Diamonds aren't forever, as
the finish have shown us,

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:55.550
but they can get you out
